Housing in the area is varied. On the one hand there are the{original } {farmhouses, cottages and village {dwellings}which have been built over the last two centuries.
On the other hand there are three areas of{local authority housing}built within the past 15 years. These were built to house the large influx of people, largely from London, who came to the area as part of{Andover's New {Town Development. }
The estates are called King Arthurs Way on which street names are taken from the legend of King Arthur, Roman Way on which street names are taken from the history of the Roman Empire and Cricketers Way on which streets are named after famous cricketers.
